east steak n shake operations inc is headquartered in indianapolis indiana there are  locations of which  are companyoperated and  are franchised typical restaurant locations have sitdown drivethru and frontwindow service resulting in a hybrid of fastfood togo service and dinerstyle sitdown service many steak n shake restaurants are open  hours a day seven days per week the menu features primarily hamburgers and handdipped milkshakes though other entrees side items and drinks are also available there is no steak on the menu the corporations slogan famous for steakburgers refers to its most prominent food item the steakburger so called because it was originally made from a mixture that included tbone sirloin and round steaks contents  history  after gus belt  biglari  franchise pricing lawsuits  locations  international expansion  west asia  europe  references  external links historyedit gus belt born in morrisonville illinois founded steak n shake in normal illinois in february  after serving four years in the united states marine corps he converted the combination gas station and chicken restaurant that he owned shells chicken into a hamburger stand the original building at the intersection of main street and west virginia avenue was damaged by a fire in the early s but it was repaired and its dining room expanded in the late s steak n shake sold this building to the monicals pizza company steak n shakes slogan in sight it must be right originally referred to belts practice of wheeling a barrel of tbone sirloin and round steaks into the public area of his restaurant then grinding them into burgers in front of his customers this practice was intended to reassure customers of the wholesomeness of the product at that time ground beef was still viewed with some skepticism by the general public based on the likelihood of its having deliberate impurities introduced into it this practice of grinding the beef in public also helped assure his customers of the veracity of belts steakburger claim because they could see for themselves that he was grinding steaks into the hamburger meat later patrons were assured that steakburgers were still made from these ingredients at our own commissary for shipment to the restaurants where the open grill line remains in sight to customers cincinnatistyle chili fiveway served over spaghetti at a steak n shake restaurant following the success of the original restaurant belt purchased a chain of goal post restaurants throughout central illinois converting them into steak n shake restaurants he also added curb service at this point after gus beltedit steak n shake continued to expand throughout illinois following the death of its creator in  with ownership passing through many hands including guss wife edith who ran the chain until  longchamps inc an east coast steakhouse company that owned the chain from  to  and the indianapolisbased franklin corporation led by robert cronin author of selling steakburgers the growth of a corporate culture after the acquisition franklin moved steak n shakes headquarters from normal illinois to indianapolis in  steak n shake and its parent company franklin were acquired by e w kelley and associates whose chairman e w ed kelley was considered largely responsible for the growth of the restaurant until his death on july   biglariedit graham rahals  indianapolis  indycar was sponsored by steak n shake franchise pricing lawsuitsedit between  and  steak n shake became involved in lawsuits with several of its franchisees concerning mandatory menu prices and mandatory food sourcing as of august update five lawsuits had been filed the first lawsuit began in  and is by stuller inc the illinois franchisee that is the oldest franchisee in steak n shakes history stuller won a preliminary injunction that went to the th circuit court of appeals in august  three more franchisees filed suit in april  — druco restaurants based in st louis people sales  profit co based in georgia and scotts ss inc in pennsylvania a settlement was reached with these franchisees in  but terms of the settlement were not made public steak n shake filed suit against denver franchisees larry and christopher baerns in july  over the same issues with a counterclaim soon after steak n shakes won their lawsuit in us district court against the baerns when judge ruled that the baerns intentionally overcharged customers the complaints by the franchisees also question whether steak n shake promised franchise results that could never actually be achieved under its policies locationsedit opening on broadway today steak n shake restaurants are located in alabama arizona arkansas california colorado florida georgia illinois indiana iowa kansas kentucky louisiana maryland michigan mississippi missouri nevada new jersey new york north carolina ohio oklahoma pennsylvania south carolina tennessee texas utah virginia washington and west virginia the first steak n shake in the state of indiana was opened as a drivein restaurant in indianapolis in november  as typical for this time period this restaurant had offered curb service carhop in additional to table service and takeout at the time of the opening of this location steak n shake had locations in five states the route  steak n shake at springfield missouri built  was listed on the national register of historic places in  the company entered north carolina for the first time by opening a franchised location in greensboro in december  after briefly operating a few restaurants in south texas during the s steak n shake returned to texas by opening locations in the dallas–fort worth area beginning in  in the houston area beginning in  and in the san antonio area beginning in  steak n shake entered south carolina for the first time by opening a location in greenville in february  the company entered oklahoma for the first time by opening a franchised location in edmond oklahoma in  steak n shake entered west virginia for the first time by opening a franchised location in barboursville in august  steak n shake opened their first location in nevada inside the south point casino in las vegas nevada in july  and second nevada location in reno in july  steak n shake entered louisiana for the first time by opening a location near baton rouge in covington louisiana in  the company first entered colorado via a franchise in denver in november  before the parent took over the colorado locations after a lengthy lawsuit between the franchisee and the parent company in january  they opened their first state of new york location in new york city adjacent to the ed sullivan theater then home to the late show with david letterman indiana native david letterman an avid steak n shake fan would frequent the location and mention it often on his show the first location in new jersey was opened by a franchise holder in september  in paramus new jersey opening of first store in seattle the first steak n shake location in the state of arizona was opened in tempe in october   the first and only location in the state of montana and in the upper plain states was opened in billings in december  this location was forced to close after two and a half years in july  due to poor sales that was blamed on harsh reviews on social media steak n shake expanded to california in july  by opening a location in victorville a los angeles county location was opened in santa monica in late october and another in burbank in december after a lack of activity for over a year in the highly competitive californian marketplace the company announced in april  of the expected opening of their first orange county location their fourth in california in aliso viejo in midmay after a short delay a fifth california location was opened behind schedule in riverside in august  in  the company had planned to open a restaurant in northern california in campbell california but local residents have been successful so far in blocking this move because of that delay the first location in northern california opened instead in daly city in november  followed by an expected opening in fresno in early  in june  the first location in maryland was opened in millersville maryland the pacific northwest saw its first location open in seattle washington in may  international expansionedit in december  steak n shake opened a corporate office in monte carlo monaco to support its expansion in west asia and europe west asiaedit in october  steak n shake announced its first international expansion agreement with plans to open forty locations in the united arab emirates the first of these locations opened in dubai in  but closed in a little more than a year ultimately only two out of the original planned  locations were opened in the united arab emirates with both being closed in january  the brand also announced in december  a unit franchise agreement in saudi arabia with ab holdings the first location in riyadh was expected to open in the first half of  the first location in the persian gulf country of kuwait was opened in december  europeedit the first two european locations were opened in cannes in france in may  and on the island of ibiza in spain in june  the second location in france was opened in marseille in december  a third location in france was opened in toulon in april  and was quickly followed in june by the openings of a fourth and fifth locations in caen and rueilmalmaison in october by the openings of a sixth location at the cité europe shopping centre in coquelles and in november of a seventh location in fenouillet the second location in spain was opened in the capital madrid in september  followed by a third location in churra murcia in october  the first location in italy was opened in milan in december  a second location was opened in peschiera del garda in may  a third location was opened in castione andevenno in september  in july  the first location in portugal was opened in montijo near lisbon in december  the first store in the united kingdom was opened in chester cheshire england referencesedit  a b c d e f history the steak n shake company archived from the original on  retrieved    biglari holdings  annual report pdf biglari holdings november   retrieved december     longchamps to buy  of restaurant concern wall street journal  p  subscription required help  alternate link via proquest  longchamps will sell steak n shake interest wall street journal  p  subscription required help  alternate link via proquest  kelley  partners acquires control of franklin corp wall street journal  p  subscription required help  alternate link via proquest  stuller inc v steak n shake enterprises inc et al  fd  th cir august   docket no   olson scott may   more franchisees join revolt over steak n shake menu pricing indianapolis business journal retrieved may     andrews greg november   settlement reached in steak n shake franchisee suit indianapolis business journal   migoya david september   judge rules steak n shakes in metro denver must close but they dont denver post   migoya david july   judge steak n shake franchise owners violated agreement must pay up federal case ends with ruling that former owners of centennial sheridan stores overcharged customers denver post   olson scott august   steak n shake dispute with franchisees reaches to denver indianapolis business journal retrieved august     opening set for thursday the indianapolis star  p  – via newspaperscom subscription required help opening of this new steak n shake drivein restaurant at  lafayette road thursday morning will mark the first appearance in indiana of the fivestate chain of restaurants four more are planned in the area   ruth keenoy january  national register of historic places inventory nomination form route  steak n shake pdf missouri department of natural resources retrieved   includes  photographs from   national register of historic places listings weekly list of actions taken on properties  through  national park