industries inc “cca industries” a manufacturer and marketer of health and beauty aids from august  to july  and since october  he has also served as a director of insignia systems inc “insignia systems” a developer and marketer of pointofpurchase instore products and services from december  to march  including its cochairman from january  to march  mr biglari is an entrepreneur with extensive managerial and investing experience in a broad range of businesses philip cooley dr philip l cooley is vice chairman of the board and a director of biglari holdings inc he is a vice chairman of the board of biglari holdings since april  and a director since march  prassel distinguished professor of business at trinity university san antonio texas from  until his retirement in may  served as an advisory director of biglari capital since  director of cca industries from august  to july  and from october  to march  of insignia systems dr cooley has extensive business and investment knowledge and experience he also has experience serving on the boards of directors of public companies bruce lewis mr bruce lewis is controller of the company he joined the company and was named controller in january  from  to  mr lewis was senior vice president and controller of blockbuster inc kenneth cooper mr kenneth r cooper is independent director of biglari holdings inc he is a director of the corporation since october  attorney in the private practice of law at the kenneth r cooper law office since  with over  years of legal and business experience in real estate transactions and related matters mr cooper has extensive experience in real estate business and financial matters james mastrian mr james p mastrian is independent director of biglari holdings inc he is a director of the corporation since august  mr mastrian was the special advisor to the chairman and chief executive officer of rite aid corporation “rite aid” from august  until his retirement in august  director of cca industries from  to august  mr mastrian served in a leadership role in the retail sector has extensive marketing experience and over  years of experience in corporate management ruth person dr ruth j person is independent director of biglari holdings inc she is a director of the corporation since  chancellor university of michiganflint from  to  and professor of management from  to present dr person has years of experience in leadership and board positions at various institutions basic compensation name fiscal year total sardar biglari  philip cooley  bruce lewis  kenneth cooper  james mastrian  ruth person  as of   dec  options compensation name options value sardar biglari   philip cooley   bruce lewis   kenneth cooper   james mastrian   ruth person   insider trading name shares traded price biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   biglari sardar   » full list on insider trading related topics stocksstock screenermarket datarestaurants  bars in biglari’s latest showdown he’s not the rabblerouser    indianapolis business journal  ibjcom  login x email password remember me forgot your password subscribe register logged in as logout edit profile view cart   quick links home » in biglari’s latest showdown he’s not the rabblerouser in biglari’s latest showdown he’s not the rabblerouser january   greg andrews keywords franchises  investing  steak n shake  banking  finance  retail  sardar biglari  real estate  retail comments print reprints  text size larger smaller x related news and opinion biglari’s buffettstyle shareholder letters colorful ‘odd’ biglari’s maxim saga drenched with drama red ink does biglari’s steak n shake storyline rewrite history irrepressible biglari runs a meeting like no one else as sardar biglari stirs controversy steak n shake hums along related products largest indianapolisarea commercial real estate brokerages  pdf largest indianapolisarea commercial real estate brokerages  excel largest indianapolisarea residential real estate agencies  pdf related events cfo of the year cto of the year activist investor sardar biglari who’s made a career out of zinging executives at underperforming public companies is about to get a taste of his own medicine groveland capital llc a minneapolisbased investment firm has filed notice with regulators that it will seek to replace biglari and biglari holdings inc’s other five directors with its own slate of nominees at the company’s annual meeting in april the move comes at a vulnerable time for sardar biglari who seized control of indianapolisbased steak n shake in  after publicly bashing management even going so far as to rent billboards along interstate  shares of san antoniobased biglari holdings inc slumped  percent last year—in part because of a controversial offering that allowed existing shareholders to buy more stock on the cheap meanwhile biglari holdings faces a raft of lawsuits from franchisees accusing the company of unlawfully mandating menu prices and from investors angry over governance practices executives at groveland which owns only about  biglari holdings shares aren’t saying what led them to turn activist a groveland representative did not respond to ibj’s inquiries but told the san antonio expressnews that because of securities and exchange commission rules it would have no comment until filing a proxy statement perhaps in february investors who buy shares in biglari holdings—which also owns the maxim men’s magazine an insurance company western sizzlin and a big stake in cracker barrel—always have known they were placing a bet with a supremely confident unconventional entrepreneur biglari sardar biglari a yearold iranianamerican makes no apologies for running his company like a fiefdom as he wrote last month in his annual letter to shareholders “capital allocation responsibility is managed exclusively by myself rather than through a committee we do not employ analysts or advisors a bureaucracy suffocates decisionmaking acuity and agility” but even some investors comfortable with giving biglari wide latitude balked after he rolled out a supersized hedgefundstyle compensation package for himself and when he proposed various maneuvers that expanded his control over company stock several investor lawsuits take aim at a  deal under which he licensed the “biglari” name to the company for  years biglari won’t receive royalties if he remains atop the company but if it were sold or if he were forced out for anything but malfeasance he’d receive  percent of sales for five years—a sum that could surpass  million the licensing agreement “is nothing more than a thinly hidden way for defendant biglari to further entrench himself … there was no apparent business purpose in naming the company after biglari in the first place other than to aggrandize defendant biglari” a  lawsuit says groveland said in a notice filed with the sec that its slate will include that firm’s founder and ceo nicholas swenson as well as ryan buckley a director at the investment banking firm livingstone partners and jim stryker a year restaurant industry veteran who formerly was chief financial officer of the tennesseebased parent of the perkins and marie callender’s chains as a matter of policy biglari doesn’t grant interviews to journalists and he did not respond to a voice mail message left at his san antonio office plenty of franchisees may get a perverse pleasure out of watching biglari squirm a bit given their animosity over his unilateral  ban on franchisees setting their own prices the move coincided with the chain’s push to ramp up customer counts by offering  meals and other bargain pricing franchisees who have filed at least four lawsuits asserting the ban is unlawful say it has put them in a financial vise as food prices rose a band of franchisees has tried to reach an amicable resolution but to no avail “in the end steak n shake made the decision to bully rather than bargain and made it clear that it would terminate any franchisee that refused to adopt the policy” according to the latest suit filed this month by mobile alabamabased eastern shore restaurants inc biglari made no mention of the legal morass in last month’s letter to shareholders which struck an upbeat tone albeit one that seemed slightly less cocksure than past letters he characterized the performance of steak n shake and western sizzlin in the latest fiscal year merely as “satisfactory” and he offered no guarantee he would succeed in reviving maxim which has rung up  million in operating losses since he bought it in february biglari hopes to turn things around by improving the magazine itself and by licensing the maxim name to a range of consumer products and services “we risk being quite wrong” he wrote in the letter “nevertheless our duty is not to avoid discomfiture but to take action after judging we have a mathematical edge anyone desiring a  probability of success best take clint eastwood’s advice in the film ‘the rookie’ ‘if you want a guarantee buy a toaster’” money to be made one reason groveland’s swenson might be swooping in is that he views biglari holdings as woefully undervalued one camp of investors using a sumofitsparts analysis wholeheartedly agrees consider this biglari holdings bought its percent stake in tennesseebased cracker barrel old country store inc from may  to december  for  million along the way biglari holdings has scooped up  million in cracker barrel dividends and the value of its stake has swelled to  million biglari holdings overall has a market capitalization of  million just  million more than the cracker barrel stake some investors say that modest number suggests the market is vastly underappreciating the value of biglari holdings’ wholly owned businesses especially steak n shake—which posted more than  million in operating earnings in the latest fiscal year despite all the franchisee unrest biglari has concrete successes he can point to at steak n shake before he took the helm the chain weathered  consecutive quarters of declining samestore sales it now is on a run of  straight quarters of increasing samestore sales in his letter biglari wrote that relentless costcutting has allowed the chain to hold the line on prices for core menu items even though beef costs alone were  million higher in the latest fiscal year than in  “our pricing philosophy is not to maximize profit per customer but to offer products at the lowest possible prices to an everincreasing number of customers” he wrote• email tweet advertisement editor behind the news columnist a native of kentucky andrews has worked at hoosier newspapers since graduating from indiana university in  he covered education at the journal and courier in lafayette before joining ibj in  he left in  to serve as statehouse reporter for the evansville courier and later served as a business reporter and the business editor of the indianapolis star he’s been writing his behind the news column for ibj since rejoining the newspaper in  outside of work andrews enjoys bicycling basketball and reading he and his wife kathleen live in indianapolis and have two sons phone  recent articles by greg andrews simon kite seek to dispel ‘retail apocalypse’ narrative itt trustee blasts firm’s former directors seeks m novel layout complicated effort to find marsh buyers for some stores please enable javascript to view the comments powered by disqus comments powered by disqus restricted content you must have javascript enabled to enjoy a limited number of articles over the next  days please clik here to continue without javascript go advanced search this weeks paper carsons in circle centre is pa